### More Did you know (auto generated)

*   ... that Indonesian ambassador [Alfred Tanduk Palembangan](/Alfred_Tanduk_Palembangan) found his calling in diplomacy through interactions with tourists? Apparently, small talk can lead to grand careers.

*   ... that medicine dean [Sjahriar Rasad](/Sjahriar_Rasad) was implicated in a conspiracy to assassinate Indonesian president [Sukarno](/Sukarno)? Intrigue is never far away.

*   ... that Indonesia's ambassador to Serbia, [Andreano Erwin](/Andreano_Erwin), joined the foreign ministry after his [trading company](/Trading_company) went belly-up? A classic tale of ambition born from failure.

*   ... that a statue honoring German-born missionary [Johann Gottlieb Schwarz](/Johann_Gottlieb_Schwarz) was commissioned by [Prabowo Subianto](/Prabowo_Subianto), who would later become president of Indonesia? History has a way of circling back.

*   ... that according to its president [Said Iqbal](/Said_Iqbal), Indonesia's [Labour Party](/Labour_Party_(Indonesia,_2021)) intends to form "personal" coalitions with presidential candidates? A rather direct approach.

*   ... that a speech penned by [Wisaksono Wirjodihardjo] for Indonesian president [Sukarno](/Sukarno) presciently cautioned against converting prime rice fields into golf courses? Foresight is a rare commodity.

