## In this month

*   A look back at significant events.

*   7 December 1975 – Indonesian troops [invade](/Indonesian_invasion_of_East_Timor) what is now [East Timor](/East_Timor), marking the commencement of a protracted 24-year occupation.

*   13 December 1937 – The Indonesian state news agency [Antara](/Antara_(news_agency)) is established. A voice for the nation, I suppose.

*   19 December 1948 – The Dutch launch [Operation Kraai](/Operation_Kraai), successfully capturing the national capital at [Yogyakarta](/Yogyakarta).

*   26 December 2004 – A catastrophic earthquake strikes north of [Aceh](/Aceh). The subsequent [tsunami](/2004_Indian_Ocean_earthquake_and_tsunami) claims at least 131,028 lives in [Indonesia alone](/Effect_of_the_2004_Indian_Ocean_earthquake_on_Indonesia). A stark reminder of nature’s indifference.

*   27 December 1949 – Following months of tense [negotiations](/Dutch%E2%80%93Indonesian_Round_Table_Conference), the Dutch formally recognize Indonesian sovereignty, effectively ending the [revolution](/Indonesian_National_Revolution).

